g?rand=46139424\" /><br />\r\n<strong>Pertama Ferroalloys Sdn. Bhd</strong>. (Formerly known as AML Manganese (Malaysia) Sdn. Bhd.) (abbreviated as &ldquo;<strong>Pertama</strong>&rdquo; hereafter) was named by the Chief Minister of the Sarawak State of Malaysia, meaning the FIRST manganese ferroalloy smelting plant in Malaysia. The plant will occupy around 200 hectares of land in the Samalaju Industrial Zone in Bintulu of the Sarawak State, Malaysia.<br />\r\n<div>\r\n	<br />\r\n	Pertama is jointly owned by Asia Minerals Limited, Nippon Denko Company Limited, Chuo Denki Kogyo Co., Ltd., Shinsho Corporation and Carbon Capital Corporation Sdn. Bhd; while Asia Minerals Limited is the majority shareholder of Pertama.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<br />\r\n	The Pertama project is a two-phase manganese alloys and ferrosilicon smelting plant development:<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<strong>Phase 1:</strong> Construction of the plant had commenced in May 2012 and production is expected to commence in the second quarter of 2015. It is also expected that full commercial production will be reached by the fourth quarter of 2015. The target annual production capacity is 250,000 metric tons.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<strong>Phase 2:</strong> Commencement of operation to be expected in the second quarter of 2018. Additional 100,000 metric tons production capacity will then be added on top of the Phase 1 development.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	To secure the supply of low cost power supply for the plant, Pertama had signed a long term Power Purchase Agreement with Syarikat Sesco Berhad in early 2012.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<br />\r\n	The final products of the plant will be manganese alloys, ferro silicon and electrolytic manganese metal (EMM). These final products will be consumed locally as well as exported to countries worldwide.</div>\r\n<br />\r\nFor more details, please visit <a href=\"http://www.pertama-fa.com\">http://www.pertama-fa.com</a>.','tb_article_details','<img src=\"/cms/upload/aml/article/b_20_3.jpg?rand=46139424\" /><br />\r\n贝塔玛合金有限公司（曾用名AML Manganese (Malaysia) Sdn. Bhd.）（简称Pertama）是由马来西亚沙捞越州的首席部长命名的，意为马来西亚首家锰合金冶炼厂。该工厂在马来西亚沙捞越州民都鲁三马拉汝工业区的占地将达到200公顷左右。<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPertama 是亚洲矿业有限公司所拥有的联合控股公司，股东还有Nippon Denko Company Limited，Chuo Denki Kogyo Co., Ltd.,Shinsho Corporation以及Carbon Capital Corporation Sdn. Bhd。亚洲矿业有限公司为主要持股人。<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPertama项目是作为锰合金工厂及硅铁冶炼工厂两个阶段来发展的<br />\r\n<br />\r\n阶段一：工厂开始于2012年建设，生产预计在2015年第二季度开始，在2015年第四个季度可以达到全面的商业化生产。目标年产量为250,000吨。<br />\r\n<br />\r\n阶段二：预计在2018年第二个季度开始运作，产量在第一个阶段的基础上额外再增加100,000吨。<br />\r\n<br />\r\n为了保证以较低的价格向工厂供电，Pertama早在2012年就与Syarikat Sesco Berhad签署了长期的购电协议。<br />\r\n<br />\r\n工厂的最终产品为锰合金，硅铁以及电解锰(EMM)，这些产品会投入到本地的市场也会出口到全球其他的国家。<br />\r\n<br />\r\n更多信息，请浏览网站<a href=\"http://www.pertama-fa.com/\">http://www.pertama-fa.com</a>.','','b_desc1'),(334,'Pertama Ferroalloys Sdn. Bhd. (Formerly known as AML Manganese (Malaysia) Sdn. Bhd.) (abbreviated as &ldquo;Pertama&rdquo; hereafter) was named...','tb_article_header','贝塔玛合金有限公司&nbsp;（曾用名AML Manganese (Malaysia) Sdn. Bhd.）（简称Pertama）是由马来西亚沙捞越州....','','a_desc'),(783,'banner6','tb_section','banner6','','l_title'),(749,'','tb_section','','','l_link'),(750,'AML is a Hong Kong based international company specializing in mineral resources businesses from ores to alloys.&nbsp; We have offices located in different countries including China, France, India, Japan, Korea, Malaysia, South Africa, Ukraine, USA, etc.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nTo cope with our business expansion, we are now inviting highcalibrecandidates to join our Hong Kong Office:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Process customers&rsquo; inquiries and make commercial offers;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Participate in commercial terms negotiation with customers, suppliers and subsidiaries sales offices;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Issue both purchase and sales contracts;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Coordinate with various internal &amp; external customers to ensure satisfactory contractual performance (including but not limited to timely production, good product quality control, timely shipment, timely payment);</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Prepare various sales or purchase reports upon request from supervisor;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Maintain and update both Customers and Suppliers Assessment Forms;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Maintain proper filing for the team; and</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Perform any ad-hoc tasks assigned by the supervisors from time to time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Job Requirements:</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		A Degree holder with major study in International Business, Trading, Marketing or related disciplines;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		At least 5 years related working experience in International Trade;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Proficient in both spoken &amp; written English and computer skills (e.g. Microsoft Office), with theoretical knowledge of INCOTERMS, with basic knowledge of international trade &amp; common trade payment terms is a must; and</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Able to work under pressure, good communication skill, positive attitude, challenging spirit, open-minded, readiness to learn and good team player.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe offer good opportunities and competitive compensation package including 5-days work, general holidays and performance bonus to the successful candidate.&nbsp; Interested parties please send a detailed resume with current and expected salary and date of availability to <a href=\"mailto:hongkong@asia-minerals.com\">hongkong@asia-minerals.com</a>.&nbsp; For further information of our company, please visit our website: <a href=\"http://www.asia-minerals.com\">http://www.asia-minerals.com</a>.&nbsp; Information provided will be kept confidential and will only be used for the recruitment related purpose.','tb_section','AML is a Hong Kong based international company specializing in mineral resource